cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes a novel pooling method for fully convolutional networks, which is a common technique used in deep learning, and thus could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses knowledge transfer between different tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve evaluating the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
